<task id="AIPU2-012" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build Capability Router Layer 1 — Keyword Classifier</title>
    <phase>2A</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, routing</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-010</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Build Layer 1 of the three-tier capability router — a zero-LLM-latency keyword classifier. It extends the
    existing AgentServiceRoutingMiddleware patterns and matches user turn text against keyword hints stored in
    each CapabilityManifestEntry. When confidence exceeds 0.8 the capability is activated directly without
    calling the LLM. This layer must handle over 60% of all turns and complete in under 50ms.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET backend engineer familiar with Spaarke AI middleware and routing patterns.</role>
  <goal>
    Layer 1 classifies over 60% of turns with confidence above 0.8, produces zero LLM calls for those turns,
    and completes within 50ms end-to-end as measured by an OTEL span.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Middleware/AgentServiceRoutingMiddleware.cs</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Capabilities/</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read AgentServiceRoutingMiddleware.cs fully to understand the middleware chain, IAgentServiceContext, and how existing routing decisions are propagated.</step>
    <step>Create CapabilityRoutingResult.cs record with: MatchedCapabilityName (string?), Confidence (float), RoutingLayer (enum: Layer1, Layer2, Layer3, None), ElapsedMs (double).</step>
    <step>Create ICapabilityRouter.cs interface with: Task&lt;CapabilityRoutingResult&gt; RouteAsync(string userTurn, CancellationToken ct).</step>
    <step>Create CapabilityRouter.cs implementing ICapabilityRouter. Layer 1 logic: normalize user turn to lowercase, tokenize on whitespace and punctuation, score each capability by counting KeywordHints matches (score = matchCount / totalHints, weighted by hint specificity), select top capability, compute confidence = topScore / (topScore + secondScore + epsilon).</step>
    <step>Add confidence threshold constant (default 0.8, configurable via IOptions&lt;CapabilityRouterOptions&gt;). If confidence &gt;= threshold, return Layer1 result immediately without calling Layer 2 or 3.</step>
    <step>Instrument with OpenTelemetry: start Activity "capability_router.layer1", set tags capability_name, confidence, matched=true|false, record duration. Emit ai_routing_layer1_hit counter and ai_routing_layer1_latency_ms histogram.</step>
    <step>Add CapabilityRoutingMiddleware.cs that sits in the AI middleware chain, calls ICapabilityRouter.RouteAsync, and writes the CapabilityRoutingResult into IAgentServiceContext for downstream services (prompt builder, tool loader).</step>
    <step>Register ICapabilityRouter (singleton), CapabilityRouter, and CapabilityRoutingMiddleware in AddAiCapabilitiesModule().</step>
    <step>Write unit tests covering: exact keyword match produces confidence &gt;= 0.8, ambiguous turn produces confidence &lt; 0.8 (falls through to Layer 2), empty turn returns None, disabled capability not matched.</step>
    <step>Run `dotnet build` and `dotnet test --filter "CapabilityRouter"` to verify.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Layer 1 returns a result in under 50ms for a manifest with 50 capabilities (verified by unit test timing).</criterion>
    <criterion>Confidence >= 0.8 for unambiguous single-capability turns (e.g. "find case law on negligence" when only one capability has "case law" hints).</criterion>
    <criterion>Confidence &lt; 0.8 for ambiguous turns — router signals fall-through to Layer 2.</criterion>
    <criterion>OTEL Activity "capability_router.layer1" emitted for every routing call.</criterion>
    <criterion>Disabled capabilities are never matched regardless of keyword overlap.</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests pass: `dotnet test --filter "CapabilityRouter"`.</criterion>
    <criterion>Build succeeds with no new warnings.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
